    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) represents a benchmark in automotive preservation. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing for a linear, high-revving power delivery. The Getrag six-speed manual gearbox offers precise shift gates, delivering torque to the rear wheels via the factory-equipped M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis exhibits exceptional structural integrity, with a documented inspection of the rear subframe mounting points and a cooling system overhaul using OEM components. Every bushing, damper, and mechanical linkage remains in peak operational state, maintaining the original factory-spec handling dynamics. This is an investment-grade specimen for the discerning purist seeking the tactile feedback of the M-division\u2019s golden era.",
